                This portfolio site is another example of my abilities. It is built using the
                <a href="https://php.net/" target="_blank">PHP</a> language with
                <a href="https://getcomposer.org/" target="_blank">Composer</a> as the package manager. It is built on the
                <a href="https://symfony.com/" target="_blank">Symfony Framework</a> with a
                <a href="https://mysql.com/" target="_blank">MySQL</a> database for the backend. On the front end, I'm using
                <a href="https://yarnpkg.com/" target="_blank">Yarn</a> for package management and
                <a href="https://github.com/symfony/webpack-encore" target="_blank">Encore</a> with
                <a href="https://webpack.github.io/" target="_blank">WebPack</a> for JS and CSS minification. While it is
                currently a very static site, my plan is to develop it into something that can easily be used by others as
                a portfolio website. In a sense, it will be a Content Management System that is very specific to developers
                and their portfolio.
            </p>
            <div class="pure-u-xl-1-24"></div>
            <section id="resume" class="pure-u-1 pure-u-xl-10-24">
                <header><h3>My Resume</h3></header>
                <p>If you would like to view my resume, I have made it available for download in multiple formats</p>
                <p class="centered">
                    <a href="{{ asset('uploads/resume/resume.pdf') }}" class="pure-button button-link"><i class="fa fa-file-pdf-o"></i> PDF</a>
                    <a href="{{ asset('uploads/resume/resume.doc') }}" class="pure-button button-link"><i class="fa fa-file-word-o"></i> Word</a>
                    <a href="" class="pure-button button-link"><i class="fa fa-file-code-o"></i> HTML</a>
